<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Onward" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Onward,</orth> 1) forward, on: <cit><quote>o. to Troy he goes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1504" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1504</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.299" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 299</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.271" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 271</bibl>.<lb />2) on the way yet to be made; opposed to behind: <cit><quote>my grief lies o. and my joy behind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 50.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 50, 14</bibl></cit>.
